Pre-Game Insights: The Toronto Blue Jays and the Atlanta Braves meet Sunday in MLB action from Truist Park.
This will be the final installment in a three-game series.
Chris Sale will take the start for the Braves on Sunday. So far Sale is 16-3 with a 2.46 ERA in 26 starts.
In the starter slot for the finale the Blue Jays will send out Yariel Rodriguez. This year in the first 17 starts of his career Rodriguez is 1-6 with a 4.61 ERA.
